1
00:00:04,642 --> 00:00:06,802
bhaktyā sañjātayā bhaktyā
[SB: 11.3.31]

2
00:00:07,028 --> 00:00:10,278
You can only get devotion 
from someone who has it.
 

3
00:00:10,549 --> 00:00:13,369
[Instructions in the Womb]

4
00:00:13,614 --> 00:00:16,550
So Prahlāda Mahārāj
responds by saying,

5
00:00:16,550 --> 00:00:19,860
matir na kṛṣṇe parataḥ svato vā

6
00:00:20,337 --> 00:00:22,977
mitho ’bhipadyeta gṛha-vratānām

7
00:00:22,977 --> 00:00:25,587
adānta-gobhir viśatāṁ tamisraṁ
 

8
00:00:25,587 --> 00:00:29,147
punaḥ punaś carvita-carvaṇānām 
[SB: 7.5.30]

9
00:00:29,147 --> 00:00:31,654
matir na kṛṣṇe parataḥ svato vā—

10
00:00:31,654 --> 00:00:34,477
you can’t get Krishna consciousness;
this what I have,

11
00:00:34,477 --> 00:00:37,967
you can’t get this
on your own.

12
00:00:41,124 --> 00:00:43,367
Guru Maharāj would say, 
“You have to connect

13
00:00:43,367 --> 00:00:46,615
with the power supply,

14
00:00:49,675 --> 00:00:51,655
the source.”

15
00:00:51,725 --> 00:00:54,873
And not only
can you not get it yourself
 

16
00:00:54,873 --> 00:00:57,053
by your own endeavors,

17
00:00:58,104 --> 00:01:02,178
even if you combine with others,
you still won’t get it;

18
00:01:02,178 --> 00:01:05,632
you won’t get it
as a group endeavor;

19
00:01:05,632 --> 00:01:08,327
you won’t get it
through democracy.

20
00:01:09,657 --> 00:01:14,045
In other words, 
it’s not ascending pluralistic democracy,

21
00:01:14,045 --> 00:01:21,745
but descending exclusive theocracy.

22
00:01:21,745 --> 00:01:27,003
Gṛha-vrat—those who have vowed,

23
00:01:27,563 --> 00:01:30,970
pledged allegiance 
to the mundane,

24
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:34,610
adānta-gobhir viśatāṁ tamisraṁ—

25
00:01:34,673 --> 00:01:37,685
then those,
whose idea of freedom

26
00:01:37,685 --> 00:01:40,596
is for the senses,
not from the senses,

27
00:01:40,596 --> 00:01:42,929
they are entering 
into deeper and deeper

28
00:01:42,929 --> 00:01:44,929
levels of darkness.

29
00:01:45,971 --> 00:01:48,217
punaḥ punaś carvita-carvaṇānām

30
00:01:48,217 --> 00:01:49,187
Doing what?

31
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:53,780
Like ‘chewing the chewed’—
over and over again.

32
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:58,747
Whatever little bit 
of apparent taste

33
00:01:58,747 --> 00:02:00,287
may have been there 
in the beginning,

34
00:02:00,287 --> 00:02:03,637
has vanished long ago.

35
00:02:03,637 --> 00:02:07,727
He says, 
na te viduḥ svārtha-gatiṁ hi viṣṇum 
 

36
00:02:08,017 --> 00:02:10,727
durāśayā ye bahir-artha-māninaḥ 
[SB: 7.5.31]

37
00:02:10,727 --> 00:02:17,513
They are thinking 
that what the heart wants—

38
00:02:18,263 --> 00:02:21,386
how to find fulfillment,
love, affection—

39
00:02:21,386 --> 00:02:26,397
that you’ll find 
in the superficial,

40
00:02:26,397 --> 00:02:28,947
the external aspect
of a thing,

41
00:02:28,947 --> 00:02:33,952
not realizing 
that it is internal culture.

42
00:02:34,482 --> 00:02:39,672
svārtha-gatiṁ hi viṣṇum
durāśayā ye bahir-artha-māninaḥ

43
00:02:39,672 --> 00:02:41,892
andhā yathāndhair upanīyamānās
 

44
00:02:41,892 --> 00:02:44,762
te ’pīśa-tantryām uru-dāmni baddhāḥ
[SB: 7.5.31]

45
00:02:44,762 --> 00:02:47,367
He said, so it’s like 
what is this world—

46
00:02:47,367 --> 00:02:50,187
it’s the blind 
leading the blind.

47
00:02:51,314 --> 00:02:53,974
What Śukadeva tells 
in the beginning of Bhāgavatam,

48
00:02:53,974 --> 00:02:55,744
apaśyatām ātma-tattvaṁ—
[SB: 2.1.2]

49
00:02:55,744 --> 00:03:00,014
those who cannot see
the self, the soul.

50
00:03:02,187 --> 00:03:07,037
For what Guru Maharāj said,
“Socrates had to die for”

51
00:03:07,247 --> 00:03:10,007
talking about the existence of ...

52
00:03:10,007 --> 00:03:16,787
Who can have no ability
to self-see, to see the self—

53
00:03:17,011 --> 00:03:21,861
it’s like the blind leading the blind.
What will be the end result?

54
00:03:24,729 --> 00:03:26,675
And what is the solution?

55
00:03:26,675 --> 00:03:29,745
naiṣāṁ matis tāvad urukramāṅghriṁ
 

56
00:03:29,745 --> 00:03:32,685
spṛśaty anarthāpagamo yad-arthaḥ

57
00:03:32,685 --> 00:03:34,785
mahīyasāṁ pāda-rajo-’bhiṣekaṁ
 

58
00:03:34,785 --> 00:03:37,535
niṣkiñcanānāṁ na vṛṇīta yāvat
[SB: 7.5.32]

59
00:03:37,535 --> 00:03:40,652
Prahlad Maharāj says,
“You have to be bathed

60
00:03:40,652 --> 00:03:47,182
in the dust of the lotus feet
of a devotee.”

61
00:03:47,512 --> 00:03:51,399
mahīyasāṁ pāda-rajo-’bhiṣekaṁ

62
00:03:51,399 --> 00:03:55,409
—an abhiṣeka of pāda-rajaḥ

63
00:03:55,409 --> 00:03:58,589
Then you can have this.

64
00:03:58,589 --> 00:04:01,230
He is trying to think, 
“Where did he get that?”

65
00:04:01,230 --> 00:04:05,510
Then we hear when Kayādhu 
was taken to the ashram of Nāradā

66
00:04:05,644 --> 00:04:12,094
that there even though 
Prahlād was in the womb, in utero,

67
00:04:12,094 --> 00:04:16,723
he’s hearing all the instructions 
of Nārada Muni.

